          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Validation_AccountRecordsWithIncorrectBillingPeriodRevision",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to validate account records and exchange data for billing period discrepancies within a SQL Server database. It checks for incorrect billing period revisions in account records and unprocessed exchange data for a specific billing period. If any discrepancies are found, it raises an error with a specific message."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
